💡 Placement Tip

In placement aptitude tests, most logarithm questions are based on identities, simplification, and change of base rather than lengthy calculations. Learn the product, quotient, and power rules, memorize common powers (such as 2⁶ = 64, 3⁴ = 81, 5⁴ = 625), and use the change of base formula whenever the base cannot be simplified directly. This approach allows you to solve most logarithm questions in under one minute.
